    public abstract class AmpFieldPanel<T>
extends AmpComponentPanel<T>
    Component to be extended directly by AMP Field Types. An AMP field contains a label with the field name, in bold, an immediately below the real form control It also holds a tooltip with help information about the field (fetched from FM Utils) The default AmpComponentPanel.fmType is obviously AmpFMTypes#FIELD
    See Also:

      • visualErrorBehavior

        protected org.apache.wicket.behavior.Behavior visualErrorBehavior()
        This is a special AjaxEventBehavior crafted for visual ajax error feedback. This can come in several flavors, for example the AbstractChoiceS is using a different kind of event, By default we use ComponentVisualErrorBehavior2
        Returns:
        the event behavior to be added to the form component, triggering ajax validation

      • addFormComponent

        protected void addFormComponent(org.apache.wicket.markup.html.form.FormComponent<?> fc)
        use this to add form components that require validation. This method initializes validation entities first, so that your component can later show an ajax style validation error. Do not use the MarkupContainer.add(org.apache.wicket.Component...) directly, this method also invokes it.
        Parameters:
        fc - The form component to have its validation entities initialized and then added as component
